doc.after: Cairo is located in northern Egypt, known as Lower Egypt, 165 kilometres (100Â mi) south of the Mediterranean Sea and 120 kilometres (75Â mi) west of the Gulf of Suez and Suez Canal.[66] The city is along the Nile River, immediately south of the point where the river leaves its desert-bound valley and branches into the low-lying Nile Delta region.
